    "Note that when LLM judges are deployed, a small number of human scores is typically available because they are used to evaluate the judge.",
    "Our work gives a recipe for learning a better judge from these scores and provides empirical support for it.",
    "Regularization: Automatic choice of the regularization strength γ by cross-validation ensures that our judges perform well on test sets in Tables 1 and 2.",
    "Without it, our judges could perform poorly.",
    "For instance, Figure 5 in Section B.2 shows that the LS judge would have a higher MSE than the base judge when the regularization strength is high."
